  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Mandatory customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Definition of money laundering offenses\n- Criminal penalties for laundering activities\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Customer identification programs\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Risk assessment protocols\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Prosecution of money laundering cases\n- International information sharing\n\n6. Specific Legal Elements\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing predicate offenses\n- Defining financial institution responsibilities\n- Creating transparency in financial transactions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
